&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/clipboard-apis/#typedefdef-clipboarditemdata"&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/clipboard-apis/#typedefdef-clipboarditemdata&lt;/a&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; Summary 
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; The ClipboardItem, which is the input to the async clipboard write 
&gt;&gt;&gt; method, now accepts string values in addition to Blobs in its constructor. 
&gt;&gt;&gt; ClipboardItemData can be a Blob, a string, or a Promise that resolves to 
&gt;&gt;&gt; either a Blob or a string.
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; Blink component Blink&gt;DataTransfer 
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/list?q=component:Blink%3EDataTransfer"&gt;https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/list?q=component:Blink%3EDataTransfer&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;  
