On Wednesday, October 30, 2024 at 3:13:13 PM UTC+1 Orr Bernstein wrote:&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

&gt; Previously we had buyerAndSellerReportingId and buyerReportingId to allow 
&gt; buyers and sellers to report information that's jointly k-anonymous with 
&gt; the other information that's reported. But we heard that people like to 
&gt; pick from a selection of reporting IDs, similar to how they pick from a 
&gt; selection of renderURLs, so we extended the API to allow storing a list of 
&gt; selectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIds in the interestGroup and selecting one 
&gt; to be reported in generateBid(). There's more detail on how and when the 
&gt; reporting IDs are provided to the reporting functions in the new section 
&gt; 5.4 of the explainer 
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#54-reporting-ids"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#54-reporting-ids&lt;/a&gt;&gt;. 
&gt; We also have these helpful onboarding docs: 
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://developers.google.com/privacy-sandbox/private-advertising/protected-audience-api/guide/reporting-id"&gt;https://developers.google.com/privacy-sandbox/private-advertising/protected-audience-api/guide/reporting-id&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;  
&gt; and 
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://developers.google.com/privacy-sandbox/private-advertising/protected-audience-api/use-case/deals"&gt;https://developers.google.com/privacy-sandbox/private-advertising/protected-audience-api/use-case/deals&lt;/a&gt;
&gt; .
&gt;
